   Linux tips &amp; tricks  
 

 

  Combining PDFs  
 
  gs   -dBATCH   -dNOPAUSE   -sDEVICE =pdfwrite  -sOutputFile =join.pdf  [ file1.pdf ]   [ file2.pdf ]  ...  [ fileN.pdf ]  

 
Regular expressions can be used instead of explicit file names, so using *.pdf at the end will join all the pdf files in the current directory.
 

 

  Instructions for ssh without retyping password every time  
 

 
 http://mah.everybody.org/docs/ssh 

 

 

    
      
   
  

  
    
